## Enforcement Rules

### Agent MUST

- ✅ Create test cases list BEFORE writing any code
- ✅ Write tests BEFORE writing implementation
- ✅ Verify test compilation failure (proves feature doesn't exist)
- ✅ Verify test execution failure (proves test is valid)
- ✅ Implement simplest code to make test pass
- ✅ Run tests after implementation to verify GREEN
- ✅ Run tests after refactoring to keep GREEN
- ✅ Run Biome after GREEN/REFACTOR phases
- ✅ Update test cases list with completion status

### Agent MUST NOT

- ❌ Write implementation before tests
- ❌ Skip REASON phase (test cases list)
- ❌ Skip verifying test failure
- ❌ Skip running tests after changes
- ❌ Delete or modify existing tests to make code pass
- ❌ Proceed without GREEN state
- ❌ Claim task complete without following all 5 steps

## Consequences of Violation

**Violating TDD = Delivering incomplete/broken code**

When agent violates TDD:
- Code quality cannot be verified
- Business requirements are not tested
- Regressions are likely to occur
- Codebase becomes fragile
- Task is considered INCOMPLETE

**The agent's job is to follow TDD, not to "finish quickly" without tests.**

