## Examples

### ❌ INCORRECT Agent Behavior

```typescript
// Agent receives task: "Create Tag entity"

// ❌ Agent writes implementation directly (NO TESTS FIRST)
export class Tag {
  constructor(private readonly name: string) {}
  getName(): string { return this.name }
}

// ❌ VIOLATION: No REASON phase, no RED phase, no tests
// This is INCOMPLETE CODE regardless of implementation quality
```

### ✅ CORRECT Agent Behavior

```typescript
// Agent receives task: "Create Tag entity"

// ✅ Step 0: REASON - Create test cases list
// File: __tests__/tag.test.ts
describe('Tag Entity', () => {
  // TEST CASES LIST (REASON)
  // 1. ✓ Create tag with valid name (simplest)
  // 2. ✓ Get tag name
  // 3. ✓ Reject empty name
  
  // ✅ Step 1: RED - Write failing test
  test('should create tag with valid name', () => {
    const tag = Tag.create({ name: 'Music' })
    expect(tag).toBeInstanceOf(Tag)
  })
  // Run test: ❌ Fails - Tag.create doesn't exist
  
  // ✅ Step 2: GREEN - Implement minimum
  // File: tag.ts
  export class Tag {
    private constructor(private readonly name: string) {}
    static create(input: { name: string }): Tag {
      return new Tag(input.name)
    }
  }
  // Run test: ✅ Passes
  
  // ✅ Step 3: REFACTOR - Improve if needed
  // (No changes needed yet)
  
  // ✅ Step 4: RE-EVALUATE - Continue to next test case
})
```

## Verification Checklist

Before marking any task as complete, verify:

- [ ] Test cases list exists in test file (REASON)
- [ ] Tests written before implementation (RED)
- [ ] Test failure verified before implementing
- [ ] Implementation makes tests pass (GREEN)
- [ ] Tests pass after refactoring (REFACTOR)
- [ ] Test cases list updated (RE-EVALUATE)
- [ ] Biome run on all edited files
- [ ] All tests passing

## Summary

**TDD is not optional. TDD is not a suggestion. TDD is MANDATORY for the agent.**

Every line of implementation code must be driven by a failing test. No exceptions.

See `.cursor/rules/tdd-cycle.mdc` for complete specification.
